<TEXT>
spiraling real estate prices last year have boosted 
japans actual assets past its gross national product for the first 
time the government said today 
the value of japans actual assets its land and structures 
rose 202 percent to 304 trillion last year while its gnp was 
287 trillion said economic planning agency chief eiichi nakao 
last years soaring prices made land assets in japan a country 
roughly the size of california worth 41 times as much as all the 
land in the united states kyodo news service said in 1986 
japanese land value was calculated at 25 times that of the united 
states 
financial assets such as equity and deposits also rose to 232 
billion a 156 percent increase over 1986 the agency said 
rapid rise in land prices and booming stock trading fueled 
the explosion of assets agency officials said 
urban land prices have stabilized somewhat in recent months 
following a series of measures by the central and local governments 
to control the spiral but prices continue to rise in fastgrowing 
suburbs 
</TEXT>
