came to beijing 
the last time chinese and indian leaders met was in 1960 when 
premier chou enlai went to new delhi two years later india and 
china fought a war over the border and china occupied a large chunk 
of indian territory 
gandhi flew into beijing accompanied by about 100 top officials 
and the two nations were expected to sign agreements on civil 
aviation border trade and science and technology 
