a cracked pipe at one of the savannah river 
plants nuclear reactors will be replaced before the reactor is 
allowed to restart us energy department officials said 
len sjostrom the department of energys acting assistant manager 
for reactor operations said replacing the pipe would not delay the 
restart scheduled for this summer because we have the time to do 
it and especially because its a smaller pipe 
all three srp reactors have been shut down since summer for 
safety improvements and maintenance they are the nations only 
source of tritium a radioactive gas used to boost the power of 
nuclear weapons 
because tritium decays 55 percent annually some federal 
officials say the nation could face forced reductions in nuclear 
weapons unless the reactors are restarted soon 
