would lead the proposed government for its full tenure and would not 
rotate his position with peres as he did in the socalled unity 
government that both parties have led since 1984 
peres would serve as finance minister while rabin would retain 
the defense ministry likud member moshe arens a former defense 
minister would serve as foreign minister 
in the proposed joint government the two parties would have an 
equal number of ministers in the decisionmaking inner cabinet 
