disciplinary code overhauled after a 1986 incident in which review 
staffers took sledgehammers to symbolic antiapartheid shanties 
excludes the president from the disciplinary process so he can speak 
out on important matters 
myerson also argued that the suspensions were far stiffer than 
those meted out to other students found guilty of disorderly 
conduct middleton countered that the misconduct may be 
unprecedented in a dartmouth classroom 
saying the editors do not have clean hands middleton noted 
