<DOCNO> AP881219-0202 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
ordinarily in the story of the first christmas 
the man of the family is subordinated as a secondary figure in 
actuality he carried out an essential and decisive role 
thats the anomaly of joseph husband of mary 
the generally scant attention given him is pointed out by 
episcopal presiding bishop edmond l browning who suggests more 
appreciation is in order for josephs heroism 
he often is omitted from our recollection of events of 
jesuss birth or portrayed unobtrusively in the background 
leaning on his staff or leading a donkey browning says in his 
christmas message 
the spotlight meanwhile is focused on mary and the child 
yet joseph guided and protected that family through dangers which 
threatened it browning says noting that it was no easy placid 
affair but one beset with troubles 
the burdens laid on joseph began when he learned to his painful 
dismay that the young woman to whom he was betrothed mary had 
become pregnant by someone else 
being a just lawabiding jew yet not wanting to put her to 
shame by openly renouncing her the account says he 
brokenheartedly resolved to divorce her quietly 
distraught and sorrowing he then had a strange dream in which an 
angel reassured him that mary was pregnant by the holy spirit and 
would bear a special son who would save people from sin 
wild or imagined joseph seized it as real and sure claiming 
mary as his bride when ordered to bethlehem for a tax registration 
he took her with him though it wasnt required possibly to shield 
her from nazareth gossip 
after they had traveled the 90 miles of dusty road and nightly 
camps with her in the late stages of pregnancy they found the town 
jammed with no room in the inn 
joseph finally found a sheltering livestock cavern and there he 
helped mary to a pallet of straw and cared for her as the child was 
born 
later joseph had another strange dream and he again acted on 
it for the sake of that child the dream was that the king had 
ordered the child killed 
rise the angelic voice warned take the child and his 
mother and flee to egypt and remain there till i tell you for 
herod is about to search for the child to destroy him 
in the middle of the night joseph roused his wife and hastily 
assembling essential gear they left with the child heading south 
toward egypt 
for many months they were refugees sleeping wherever they 
could surviving on what he could earn on work gangs or otherwise 
but he somehow provided for his family 
eventually through another dream joseph decided they could 
safely return and they did so making that long trip back to 
nazareth 
there as jesus reached boyhood joseph took over teaching him 
prayers blessings scripture and the carpentry trade 
when a lad of l2 jesus showed an independent streak getting 
absorbed in conversing with temple scholars in jerusalem while his 
parents hunted him for three days before finding him 
joseph the patient carpenter was ever gods obedient 
servant browning says responding to each crisis to protect and 
shield mary and the child browning adds 
joseph was called by god to do what was socially unacceptable 
in taking a pregnant mary into his house he was unable to find a 
suitable place for her to give birth 
he led his family into exile he had to begin a new life 
joseph is an important part of our understanding of the incarnation 
because he helps remind us that god entered into the very core of 
humanity 
joseph reminds us that god often calls the most lowly and the 
most unlikely to be instruments of salvation joseph reminds us that 
our relationships may not always be troublefree or happy but they 
can be holy 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

