christmas now is drawing near saydisc sneaks noyse 
thys yool nimbus the martin best ensemble 
christmas night collegium the cambridge singers and the 
city of london sinfonia john rutter conducting 
 
sneaks noyse a british early music group promises that its 
carol collection is done with original instruments rebecs 
pennywhistles citterns and such and at first it may sound as if 
the consort includes a cat doing its death rattle 
oh christmas now is drawing near the singers drone doing 
their best to sound like tipsy amateurs out yowling for drinks and 
mince pies 
patience however will be rewarded among the 28 tunes is a 
lovely version of sweet was the song the virgin sang a 
littleheard carol written down in the early 17th century theres 
an unfamiliar tune collected in 1952 for the holly and the 
ivy and some delightful instrumentals fy nay prithee john 
and the furry day carol 
if you must know what furry day is the brief notes are no help 
to get the most from the recording the listener ought to be reading 
along in the oxford book of carols the handiest source of 
seasonal musical lore the book explains that furry is from the 
latin feria which means holiday also the root of the word 
fair as in village fair 
lucie skeaping the soprano for sneaks noyse also appears on 
thys yool a more austere christmas recording from the martin best 
ensemble 
one of the jewels in this collection is a 14thcentury song as 
i lay on yoolis night in which the narrator imagines being 
present at the nativity sing now mother said the child 
about what shall befall me hereafter when i become old 
the mother responds with an eloquent shrug sweet son 
wherefore should i sing i never knew anymore about you but what 
gabriel told me in his greeting 
on the rollicking side theres the song tapster drynker 
which is simply an appeal for one more round 
after the austerities of authentic antiquity as presently 
understood john rutters polished collection of standards is balm 
for the ears rutter one of the rising stars in british choral 
music both as a composer and conductor serves up familiar favorites 
starting with in dulci jubilo and on through adam lay 
ybounden the cherry tree carol and even one dreads o 
tannenbaum 
wretched sentimentality is avoided however by the 
professionalism and the sincerity of the performances 
by robert barr associated press writer 
</TEXT>
