optimism of the title tune cowritten with shear and ends with the 
angry mann adding an expletive to the line life could be great 
that concludes believed you were lucky 
the natural temptation is to run in panic when you hear one of 
the songs is titled j for jules and features a french horn 
somehow she makes it work mann is an imaginative writer able to 
give a new twist to an old subject and her mournful voice is 
brightened by strong pop melodies 
i was counting to forever and never even got to 10 she sings 
at one point when we found a rip in heaven we should have just 
ascended then 
