this woman rca kt oslin 
 
kt oslin who began her recording career at the age of 45 has 
soared to country music stardom on the basis of her excellent 
songwriting and a strong expressive voice 
those strengths as well as a glaring weakness squeakyclean 
middleoftheroad pop arrangements that undercut the gritty 
reallife images of her lyrics are served up in equal measures on 
this woman 
the followup to 80s ladies her smash 1987 debut this 
woman features nine songs that look knowingly at the good times 
bad times and silly games that make and break relationships 
the best songs include jealous in which the singer fumes 
over a man who doesnt know shes alive while he runs after another 
woman who doesnt know hes alive oslins growling angry vocal 
burning through a gorgeous piano melody cannot be ignored 
and where is a woman to go offers a hangin out at the bar 
tale from a womans perspective you know my daddy would die if he 
knew his baby was seekin refuge in a little ol bar cross town 
she sings but tell me where is a woman to go when shes feeling 
low 
in fact theres not a number on the album that really can be 
called bad but a nagging feeling persists how would these songs 
sound with a nice little roughedged band behind oslin 
next time out someone get this woman such a band 
by marc rice associated press writer 
