<TEXT>
the strangest hit of the holiday season is a 
gagpacked feature version of a television series that lasted only 
four weeks starring an actor better known for playing villains than 
getting laughs 
leslie nielsen who has a long record of evildoing in films and 
television is currently killing people with laughs in the naked 
gun from the files of police squad the paramount pictures 
release is the work of jerry zucker jim abrams and david zucker 
who previously made airplane and who specialize in titles and 
scripts with exclamation marks 
nielsen 62 repeats the role of lt frank drebin the incredibly 
incompetent detective who appeared in the brief lamented 1982 
series police squad the actor who had appeared in 
airplane recalled the inception of the show 
jerry and jim and david invited me to lunch and they even 
pitched me they didnt realize i was putty in their hands anything 
they wanted me to do i was willing 
they mentioned doing police squad on television can you 
imagine me doing lt drebin on tv under the auspices of the zuckers 
and abrams paradise 
sad to say abc yanked police squad after six chapters were 
made and four aired why 
it didnt belong on tv nielsen theorized it had the kind 
of humor you have to pay attention to when you have a screen that 
is bigger than life you can see what is going on in the background 
you dont have to search for it 
you can watch it at home and look around and say gee im 
going to get that door painted or leave the telephone alone 
there was no laugh track to bring the audiences attention back to 
the screen it belongs up there on the big screen in theaters 
where people have paid money to get in so theyre not liable to 
waste their money by not paying attention 
nielsen explained that zaz as the trio are called originally 
planned to make a feature of police squad but couldnt find a 
plot long enough so they fashioned miniplots for a tv series 
after years of trying they came up with a story that pitted drebin 
against vincent ludwig ricardo mantalban the los angeles 
businessman who is really a killer 
a large part of the appeal of naked gunpolice squad can be 
attributed to nielsens straightarrow playing of the outrageous 
events there is a certain madness in his method the more 
seriousness the more credibility you present in your demeanor when 
youre talking about insanity the funnier it becomes 
although he was something of a practical joker as a boy in fort 
norman saskatchewan we didnt know that water bombs would freeze 
on the way down from a secondstory window leslie nielsen was 
not considered much of a comedian in his early years one of three 
sons of a royal canadian mountie he served as a gunner in the royal 
canadian air force and later studied at lorne greenes radio academy 
in toronto 
winning a scholarship to new yorks neighborhood playhouse 
nielsen moved into live television appearing on 46 shows in one 
year his first movie was the title role in the vagabond king 
mgm signed him to a term contract but he never rose from playing 
leads in b pictures and secondleads in major films 
moving into television he specialized in heavies in episodic 
tv they always needed a guest star he said the star was always 
the good guy so the best part was the heavy the meaner and more 
ferocious you were the better the hero looked when he whipped you 
he also briefly starred in his own series 
i began with the new breed and we did 36 shows in one year 
then i did brackens world the bold ones and swamp fox at 
disney also shaping up and police squad none of them went over 
a year some had only six shows or less 
but maybe it worked out all right in the long run he said 
because now im doing the naked gun and i dont have any track 
record with any one character thats endured 
after 35 years in hollywood i finally realized that i had been 
cast against type ive finally found my home as lt frank 
drebin 
the success of naked gun will undoubtedly lead to a sequel 
already they were working on a script nielsen disclosed 
ill be meeting in the oval office with president bush who will 
send me to catch mr big in the drug trade i will be working 
directly with the mastermind of the antidrug campaign vice 
president quayle theyre thinking of asking pat sajak to play that 
part 
of course mr big will turn out to be ricardo mantalban he 
died in naked gun but his evil twin is out there lurking they 
may even call it the wrath of ludwig 
he could be serious 
