<TEXT>
twentyone years ago the chicago transit 
authority came to mean a rock band as well as elevated trains around 
the loop but the group had to shorten its name to chicago when sued 
by the windy citys mayor richard j daley 
now the sevenman chicago which numbers its record albums rather 
than names them has 19 in the top 100 on cashbox magazines 
bestselling chart a single from 19 look away moved 
into the top 10 the first single from the album i dont wanna 
live without your love charted in the top 10 in august 
chicago having survived the death of guitarist terry kath peter 
ceteras leaving for a solo career and a slump is going strong 
i think you have a sophisticated and educated listener said 
woodwinds player walt parazaider more people are musical than in 
the late 60s and 70s whether the crowd knows a b flat from a z 
diminished they know if youre not playing well 
chicago has had time to learn to play well as we sit here 21 
years later five of the six originals are still in the band six 
months after we began we added peter cetera as bassist and lead 
vocalist parazaider said 
the idea danny drummer danny seraphine and i had was lets 
put together a rock n roll band with horns wed incorporate horns 
as more than background licks i think weve kept up with that 
the group has had time to get jaded too but parazaider says 
that hasnt happened they say weve sold 80to100 million 
records and had something like 33 top 40 hit singles 
every time i hear about a hit record thats a thrill heres 
people buying your music something that you create theres no 
jaded part to chicago we are thoroughly pleased that people enjoy 
what were doing 
from their first album in 1969 chicago transit authority 
the group became a big underground success and became known as a 
touring band 
janis joplin and jimi hendrix took us on tour as opening act 
before we had a record parazaider said recalling that hendrix 
told him your horn section is like one set of lungs and your 
guitar player is better than me joplin told him when you get 
as famous as im going to be and you will dont take it too 
serious 
it meant a lot to me a link to people that are legends 
parazaider said that they respected us is great i feel fortunate 
we touched base with them at all we take it serious but this isnt 
brain surgery 
touring he said has always been one of chicagos strengths 
the music we play on stage is free but traveling they cant pay 
us enough for that we do tours of 130 shows in 150 days were 
always out there playing for whoever wants to hear us you get 
